message.content: Based on the process list extracted from the memory image, the process "AcroRd32.exe" (Adobe Acrobat Reader) is the most likely responsible for the initial exploit. The suspicious PDF file that the employee opened could have exploited a vulnerability in Adobe Acrobat Reader, leading to the installation of malware or a backdoor on the system. Further analysis of the memory image should focus on this process to identify any malicious activities or artifacts associated with the suspected exploit.
